This text was unquestioningly adopted by later editions, without so much as an indication of the manuscript readings at many such places. Nevertheless, despite the alterations made by editors, the main body of the text is clear in all the manuscripts con- sulted, and the area of disputable readings, significant or in- significant, is only about eight hundred words out oi a total of over twelve thousand.

In basing the text on ΑΒ, the best group of the MSS. 'fl-K, it becomes clear that while there are no difficulties in the form ol lacunae or corrupt passages ol extended length, there are many readings, principally of individual words, which need exact determination. All these readings have been minutely examined and tested by the weight oi the manuscript evidence available and a comparison ol the usage oi Possidius in other instances.
